Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Rongcheng%20Shidaowan%20reactor%20is%20officially%20being%20used%20to%20supply%20power%20to%20the%20regional%20grid%20after%20a%20168-hour%20test%2C%20the%20administration%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20only%20capable%20of%20producing%20around%20200%20megawatts%20of%20electricity%2C%20compared%20to%20other%20plants%20like%20the%20Grand%20Gulf%20reactor%20in%20Port%20Gibson%2C%20Mississippi%2C%20which%20is%20a%201%2C433%20megawatt%20unit%20and%20the%20most%20powerful%20reactor%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fukushima%20plant%20in%20Japan%20had%20six%20reactors%20producing%204.69%20gigawatts%2C%20while%20Russia's%20BN-1200%20reactor%20in%20Beloyarsk%20produces%201%2C200%20megawatts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Shidaowan's%20claim%20to%20fame%20is%20how%20it%20generates%20power.%20The%20reactor%20is%20cooled%20using%20helium%20gas%20instead%20of%20water%20%E2%80%94%20a%20boon%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fbeijing-olympics-artificial-snow-costs-days-drinking-water-900-million-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%20as%20it%20struggles%20to%20find%20ample%20water%20for%20its%20people.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReactors%20typically%20need%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-pub.iaea.org%2FMTCD%2FPublications%2FPDF%2FP1569_web.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E400%20to%20720%20gallons%20of%20water%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20every%20megawatt%20produced%20for%20an%20hour%2C%20meaning%20a%20single%20nuclear%20plant%20can%20use%20billions%20of%20gallons%20per%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperimental%20reactors%20using%20helium%20have%20been%20built%20before%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jaea.go.jp%2F04%2Fo-arai%2Fen%2Fresearch%2Fresearch_03.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20in%20Oarai%2C%20Japan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20the%20Shidaowan%20is%20the%20first%20to%20be%20used%20commercially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20capable%20of%20shutting%20down%20automati